                  <div class="wpb_wrapper">
            
    <div class="wpb_text_column wpb_content_element ">
        <div class="wpb_wrapper">
            <p><span style="font-weight: 400;">For investments, there are two components: yield (income) and growth. Yield is the money you make and growth is the projection or rate of the income increasing over time. As a rule of thumb, investments with a high yield usually have low expected growth, and investments offering a low yield will tend to have high expected growth.&nbsp;</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Here are some of the top-rated forms of high yield investments:</span></p>

