<ul>
<li style="opacity: 1; left: 0px;"><i class="icon-default-style icon-salient-thin-line accent-color"></i> <span style="font-weight: 400;"><strong>Startup investments</strong> – The introduction of crowdfunding in startups is gaining popularity and if your investment is at the seed-level, your financial contribution can also bring innovation to the business which is exciting. The <a href="https://www.venturecrowd.com.au/s/high-return-investments">return on your investment</a> will depend on the stage of the startup and of course, how much money you put in.&nbsp;</span></li>
<li style="opacity: 1; left: 0px;"><i class="icon-default-style icon-salient-thin-line accent-color"></i> <span style="font-weight: 400;"><strong>Venture Capital</strong> – There is the option to invest in one or more publicly-traded </span><a href="https://www.venturecrowd.com.au/s/venture-capital"><span style="font-weight: 400;">venture capital</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> firms. VentureCrowd focuses on making principal investments and managing funds for seed-stage and early-stage ventures. </span><a href="https://www.venturecrowd.com.au/s/angel-investing"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Angel investing</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> also follows similar principles.</span></li>
<li style="opacity: 1; left: 0px;"><i class="icon-default-style icon-salient-thin-line accent-color"></i> <span style="font-weight: 400;"><strong>High yield bonds</strong> – Also called ‘junk bonds’ which is a&nbsp;fixed income instrument that represents a loan made by an investor to a borrower. These bonds are considered high yield investments as they pay high-interest rates because there is a greater risk of them defaulting.</span></li>
<li style="opacity: 1; left: 0px;"><i class="icon-default-style icon-salient-thin-line accent-color"></i> <span style="font-weight: 400;"><strong>Initial Public Offering (IPOs)</strong> – This is a type of public offering where shares of a company are sold to investors. An IPO is underwritten by banks that arrange for the shares to be listed on stock exchanges.</span></li>
</ul>
